         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>
               A short theological treatise. It was probably translated from a Greek Vorlage. It is found in many manuscripts together with other
               Ethiopian theological and liturgical treatises, such as the Ethiopic
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2461Testam">Testamentum
                                                  Domini</t:ref> (as  <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2461Testam#Chapter22">Chapter 22</t:ref>),
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1586Hayman">Hāymānota
                                                  ʾabaw</t:ref>, and <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1544Gebrah">Gǝbra Ḥǝmāmāt</t:ref>.
               Sometimes it is bound together with the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1960Mashaf">Maṣḥafa
                                                  qǝddāse</t:ref>.</t:p>
            <t:p>Not to be confused with the text also known as <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3978Elmastoagya">ʾƎlmasṭoʾagya</t:ref>.
            For texts in the versions that cannot be immediately identified, see
            <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6688TeachingMysteries">Teaching of
                                                  Mysteries (general record)</t:ref>.
            </t:p>
         </t:abstract>

